ced\n\nIn this example, we use a composable that detects the user's default locale from the HTTP request headers and keeps it in a `locale` state.\n\n:LinkExample{link=\"/examples/other/locale\"}\n\n## Shared state\n\nBy using [auto-imported composables](/guide/directory-structure/composables) we can define global type-safe states and import them across the app.\n\n```ts [composables/states.ts]\nexport const useCounter = () => useState<number>('counter', () => 0)\nexport const useColor = () => useState<string>('color', () => 'pink')\n```\n\n```vue [app.vue]\n<script setup>\nconst color = useColor() // Same as useState('color')\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <p>Current color: {{ color }}</p>\n</template>\n```\n","ast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"prose-h1","props":{"class":"d-heading-title","id":"state-management"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"State Management"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-paragraph","props":{"class":"d-heading-description"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Nuxt provides "},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"useState"}]},{"type":"text","value":" composable to create a reactive and SSR-friendly shared state across components."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-paragraph","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"prose-code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"useState"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is an SSR-friendly "},{"type":"element","tag":"prose-a","props":{"href":"https://vuejs.org/api/reactivity-core.html#ref","rel":["nofollow","noopener","noreferrer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"prose-code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ref"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":" replacement. Its value will be preserved after server-side rendering (during client-side hydration) and shared across all components using a unique key."}]},{"type":"text","